<item>
            <title>[JCR-1715] Prevent excessive Path.Element instances</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1715</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Even when a CachingHierarchyManager is used jackrabbit creates a lot of Path.Element instances. The internally used PathMap (spi-commons) creates new Path.Element instances whenever a path is constructed, even when the path is constructed from cached PathMap.Elements.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Running a test with 10k nodes results in 250k Path.Element instances being created and held in memory (mostly for events).</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12401998">JCR-1715</key>
            <summary>Prevent excessive Path.Element instances</summary>
